    pushback: { challenge: "What if the board can be 1D (single row or column)?", options: ["Algorithm handles it automatically — border check includes all cells in 1-row/1-column board. Every cell is a border cell. Nothing gets flipped.","Need special case","DFS breaks for 1D"], correct: 0, explanation: "1-row board: every cell is in row 0 (top border) AND row m-1 (bottom border). All 'O's are border cells → all marked safe. Nothing flipped. Algorithm handles this correctly with no special case." },
